{% extends "base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Leveling Mining{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<h1>Leveling Mining</h1>
<p>The Mining skill is one of nine player skills in Cubic Odyssey (confirmed by <code>data/configs/achievements/max_level_mining.cfg</code>). It governs how quickly you break voxel-tier ores and how much ore you recover per swing.</p>

<div class="section-grid">
<div>

<h2>How XP is earned</h2>
<p>Mining XP comes from <strong>breaking ore voxels</strong> — every successful mining hit that lands on a block in category <code>E_VCAT_ORES</code> (the 26 ores listed on <a href="{{ root }}ores.html">the Ores page</a>) credits Mining experience. Non-ore voxels (Stone, Limestone, Cliff, Lava etc.) do not. Higher-tier ores award more XP per block.</p>

<h2>Step 1 — Always carry the best mining laser you can use</h2>
<p>There are 8 mining lasers in the game. Each has a <code>voxel_tier</code> stat that caps the ore tier it can break:</p>

<table class="wiki">
<thead><tr><th class="icon"></th><th>Laser</th><th class="numeric">Voxel tier</th><th>Mines up to</th><th class="numeric">DPS hint</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for l in lasers %}
<tr>
    <td class="icon">{% if l.icon %}<img src="{{ root }}{{ l.icon }}" alt="">{% endif %}</td>
    <td><a href="{{ root }}tools/{{ l.slug }}.html">{{ l.display }}</a></td>
    <td class="numeric"><span class="tier tier-{{ l.tier }}">T{{ l.tier }}</span></td>
    <td>{{ l.mines_up_to }}</td>
    <td class="numeric mono">{{ l.dps_hint }}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-faint)">Note: Mining Laser 6 and 7 share <code>voxel_tier 7</code>; laser 7 has higher fire rate and damage so it mines faster but doesn't unlock new ores. Both can crack <a href="{{ root }}ores/res_glowing_iron_ore.html">Glowing ores</a> and Higgs Bosson.</p>

<h2>Step 2 — Match ore tier to your skill, not to your laser</h2>
<p>Your laser determines which ores you <em>can</em> mine; your skill level (combined with the laser's <code>voxel_damage</code> and <code>fireRateRPM</code>) determines how <em>fast</em>. The most efficient grind is mining a tier you can break in under 2 seconds per block.</p>

<div class="kvs">
<dl>
    <dt>Tier 1 (early)</dt><dd>{{ ores_by_tier.get(1, [])|map(attribute='display')|join(', ') }} — sub-second breaks even with Mining Laser 0.</dd>
    <dt>Tier 2</dt><dd>{{ ores_by_tier.get(2, [])|map(attribute='display')|join(', ') }} — switch to laser 1.</dd>
    <dt>Tier 3</dt><dd>{{ ores_by_tier.get(3, [])|map(attribute='display')|join(', ') }} — laser 2.</dd>
    <dt>Tier 4</dt><dd>{{ ores_by_tier.get(4, [])|map(attribute='display')|join(', ') }} — laser 3 minimum, laser 4 preferred.</dd>
    <dt>Tier 5 (gems)</dt><dd>{{ ores_by_tier.get(5, [])|map(attribute='display')|join(', ') }} — laser 4 minimum.</dd>
    <dt>Tier 6 (Matter)</dt><dd>{{ ores_by_tier.get(6, [])|map(attribute='display')|join(', ') }} — laser 5+. These are rare-spawn end-game ores.</dd>
    <dt>Tier 7 (Glowing / Higgs)</dt><dd>{{ glowing_count }} Glowing variants, plus Higgs Bosson — laser 6 or 7.</dd>
</dl>
</div>

<h2>Step 3 — Backpack tier multiplies efficiency</h2>
<p>Each tier of <a href="{{ root }}tools.html">backpack</a> increases inventory capacity. Running back to a refinery every few veins wastes mining time. Backpack 5 is the realistic late-game target — see <a href="{{ root }}guides/motherboards.html">the Motherboards guide</a> for the materials it eats.</p>

<h2>Step 4 — Pick the right planet type</h2>
<p>Ore concentration varies wildly between planet types. Use the <a href="{{ root }}ores.html">ores table</a> to filter by tier, then click into an ore to see its location table. Quick highlights:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Earth-like worlds</strong> (Earth, Bardwell I–III) host every tier-1 and tier-2 ore in good density. Best starter loop.</li>
    <li><strong>Crystalline worlds</strong> are the gem (T5) hotspot.</li>
    <li><strong>Scorched worlds</strong> stack rare-matter ores (T6) and Glowing variants.</li>
    <li><strong>Barren worlds</strong> are good for T3–T4 (Magnetite, Cobalt) without the danger of scorched / xeno biomes.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Tips that compound</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Mine in vertical shafts.</strong> Frequency (<code>m_frequency</code>) is the same across all Y-layers for most ores, but vein extent (<code>m_extent</code>) is highest in the deep layers. Drop a shaft to bedrock and mine outward.</li>
    <li><strong>Don't sell ore — smelt it.</strong> The <a href="{{ root }}ingots.html">ingot</a> form is worth more than the raw ore and is what crafting wants anyway.</li>
    <li><strong>Glowing ores aren't just shinier — they're a separate tier-7 drop.</strong> They smelt into Glowing Ingots used in late-game crafting.</li>
    <li><strong>Mining skill XP rewards are global</strong> — there's no per-planet cap. Pick a deep iron vein on Earth and grind cleanly.</li>
</ul>

</div>

<aside class="infobox">
<h3 style="margin-top:0">At a glance</h3>
<dl>
    <dt>Skill</dt><dd>Mining</dd>
    <dt>Activity</dt><dd>Breaking ore voxels</dd>
    <dt>Best tool family</dt><dd><a href="{{ root }}tools.html">Mining Lasers</a> (8 tiers)</dd>
    <dt>Best ore for grind</dt><dd>Iron / Coal (tier 1) early; Cobalt / Uranium (tier 4) mid; Diamond / Ruby (tier 5) late.</dd>
    <dt>Capacity multiplier</dt><dd>Backpack tier</dd>
    <dt>Achievement</dt><dd class="mono">ACH_MAX_LEVEL_MINING</dd>
</dl>
</aside>
</div>

